The paper proposes a novel method for multi-label learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The method involves structured decomposition and group sparsity, which are techniques commonly used in areas such as computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also evaluates the method on several real datasets, which suggests a focus on practical applications, placing it in the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, which encompasses a broad range of machine learning topics.
